Vietnam has launched a support fund for victims of war-era defoliant, focusing on areas with high rates of birth defects and cancers.
The Red Cross initiated the fund, aiming to address the lingering effects of dioxin exposure.
Despite ongoing research, conclusive links between herbicides and certain illnesses remain elusive.
The Vietnamese government plans a nationwide census of Agent Orange victims, with a focus on central and northern provinces.
Efforts to study the long-term impacts of herbicides are hindered by limited data and conflicting research findings.
The legacy of Agent Orange continues to impact generations, highlighting the need for ongoing support and research.
